Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Place @Cajun Chicken Wings{18%ounce} on a lightly oiled, foil-lined #baking sheet{}. Bake on middle rack for ~{15%minutes}. Flip wings and cook until wings are lightly browned and crispy, ~{10%minutes} more.

Empty contents of @Sweet Kale Salad Kit{1} into a large #bowl{}. Drizzle with as much dressing as you like, then toss to evenly coat. Serve.

> Is there anything more craveable than chicken wings? Answer: Chicken wings and a kale salad! The wings are coated in a savory blend of kickin' Cajun spices and are crispy on the outside and super-juicy on the inside. They pair perfectly with a crunchy salad that's positively bursting with kale, green cabbage, broccoli, Brussels sprouts, chicory, roasted pumpkin seeds, and dried cranberries, all tossed in a savory-sweet poppy seed dressing.